    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-saag-gosht-style-beef-meatballs-and-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle, then peel and finely chop (or grate) <strong>half</strong> your <strong>garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> in a bowl with your <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>mince </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until thoroughly combined (clean hands is the best way!), then divide equally and shape into 6 small meatballs per person</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-saag-gosht-style-beef-meatballs-and-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach </strong>then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool, then once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p><p>Chop your <strong>green chilli</strong> in half</p><p>Crush the <strong>remaining garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-saag-gosht-style-beef-meatballs-and-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until browned</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-saag-gosht-style-beef-meatballs-and-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>green chilli</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) to a <strong>food processor </strong>with the<strong> crushed garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger paste</strong>, <strong>curry powder </strong>and most of your <strong>coriander </strong>(save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>saag paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-saag-gosht-style-beef-meatballs-and-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the meatballs are browned, add the <strong>saag paste</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-saag-gosht-style-beef-meatballs-and-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> to the pan with 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 15-18 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!), stirring occasionally \u2013 these are your <strong>spicy saag gosht-style meatballs</strong></p><p>Slice the<strong> remaining green chilli</strong> into rounds</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-saag-gosht-style-beef-meatballs-and-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy saag gosht-style meatballs </strong>with the<strong> cooked rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle over your <strong>yoghurt </strong>and dollop on your<strong> mango chutney</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> reserved coriander leaves </strong>and the <strong>chilli rounds </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
